This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama in 2011. The memorandum is regarding the designation of officers of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation (OPIC) to act as the President of OPIC in the event that the current President is unable to perform their duties. The memorandum lists the order of succession for these officers and includes exceptions and provisions for the designation of an acting President. The memorandum also revokes a previous presidential memorandum from 2009 and states that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits. The memorandum concludes by authorizing its publication in the Federal Register.